					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A few notes about how it will look on an NTSC TV:<br /><br />1. Aspect ratio has nonsquare pixels. Expect it to be a little wider looking.<br /><br />2. Horizontal detail gets blurred slightly, and colours bleed over each other. It helps to make text or other important visual details at least 2 pixels wide.<br /><br />3. Scanlines have underlying patterns that produce colours unevenly across the screen, which means that things like 50% dither (&quot;checkerboard&quot; arrangement of pixels) will take on ripple artifacts (<a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=21&amp;t=11313" class="postlink">example</a>). This also causes detailed background to &quot;shimmer&quot; under smooth scrolling conditions (<a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=12198" class="postlink">discussion</a>).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

